  <shuffleanswers>1</shuffleanswers>
  <answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>\(0\)</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>Siempre positiva.</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>Igual a la longitud de \(C\).</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>Igual al área encerrada por \(C\).</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
</question>
<question type="multichoice">
  <name format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[CC-Grad-01]]></text>
  </name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>Decir que un campo vectorial \(\vec {F}\) «proviene de un gradiente» significa que existe un campo escalar \(f\) tal que: </p>]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <defaultgrade>1.0</defaultgrade>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text/></generalfeedback>
  <penalty>0.10</penalty>
  <hidden>0</hidden>
  <single>true</single>
  <shuffleanswers>1</shuffleanswers>
  <answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>\(\vec {F} = \nabla f\)</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>\(\vec {F} = \nabla \cdot f\)</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>\(\vec {F} = \nabla \times f\)</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>\(f = \nabla \vec {F}\)</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
</question>
<question type="multichoice">
  <name format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[CC-Grad-02]]></text>
  </name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>Si \( F\colon \mathbb {R}^3 \rightarrow \mathbb {R}^3\) proviene de un gradiente (es conservativo), entonces necesariamente su rotacional cumple: </p>]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <defaultgrade>1.0</defaultgrade>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text/></generalfeedback>
  <penalty>0.10</penalty>
  <hidden>0</hidden>
  <single>true</single>
  <shuffleanswers>1</shuffleanswers>
  <answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>\(\nabla \times \vec {F} = \vec {0}\)</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>\(\nabla \times \vec {F} \neq \vec {0}\)</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>\(\nabla \cdot \vec {F} = 0\)</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>\(\nabla \cdot \vec {F} = 1\)</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
</question>
<question type="multichoice">
  <name format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[CC-Grad-03]]></text>
  </name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>¿Cuál de las siguientes condiciones permite reconocer que un campo \(\vec {F}=(P,Q)\) de clase \(C^1\) podría provenir de un gradiente en un dominio simplemente conexo? </p>]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <defaultgrade>1.0</defaultgrade>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text/></generalfeedback>
  <penalty>0.10</penalty>
  <hidden>0</hidden>
  <single>true</single>
  <shuffleanswers>1</shuffleanswers>
  <answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>\(\dfrac {\partial P}{\partial y} = \dfrac {\partial Q}{\partial x}\)</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>\(\dfrac {\partial P}{\partial x} = \dfrac {\partial Q}{\partial y}\)</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>\(P = Q\)</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p>\(\dfrac {\partial P}{\partial x} + \dfrac {\partial Q}{\partial y} = 0\)</p>]]></text>
  </answer>
</question>
 
